cs.LO, cs.AI, cs.PL, cs.CC, cs.DS

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a logic of interactive proofs as a framework for an intuitionistic foundation for interactive computation. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper discusses the transfer of propositional knowledge in multi-agent distributed systems, which is a common topic in AI research. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is relevant as the paper discusses the Curry-Howard isomorphism between intuitionistic proofs and typed programs. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is relevant as the paper discusses the equipotence of non-interactive and interactive computation. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses computation and proof systems.
